					<description><![CDATA[<p>Jan 28, 1907 Los Angeles Ã¢â‚¬Å“If my career seems strange to you, it seems stranger and more incredible to me,Ã¢â‚¬Â Gen. Homer Lea once said. And indeed it was, for LeaÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s life was the tale of a badly handicapped boyÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s adventures as a leader in an exotic foreign land. His 1912 obituary in The Times&#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://https://pensive-torvalds-020d34.netlify.app/2007/01/28/a-most-remarkable-man/">Continue reading <span class="screen-reader-text">A Most Remarkable Man</span></a></p>
